narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: This class was invaluable to me in many ways. I was able to get the advice from Professor Dudley--a profound, brilliant and kind professor--on my research. I was able to also get advice from my interlocutors...and often we dont have the time to really sit down and work with one another. In this context, I gained new insights from my peers both concerning my work and in collaborating with them to give advice on other peoples work. Really, such a valuable class!

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: The class is wonderful. The Professor's plan for the course is wonderful. I think attendance should be mandatory.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes! A wonderful space to think through new ideas and forms of ethnography
Yes, any student that wants a supportive and informative space to develop their work and to help develop the work of others should go here.
